cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CL

The paper discusses the application of generic summarization algorithms to music, which involves techniques from information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) fields. Therefore, cs.SD (Sound) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for genre classification, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of text-based algorithms for music summarization, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
